These two scripts set up a rudimentary backup system for a Drupal site that has everything in /sites/all and /sites/default/files

It will not back up the settings files.  This should be fine: you can create a new settings file, and the database information is probably new anyway.


# Amazon S3

> sudo apt-get install python-pip

> sudo pip install boto

Set up a bucket

Set up a user

Grant access to the bucket

chmod 500 backup.cfg
